# Calculating risk-weighted exposure amounts and expected loss amounts under the Financial Collateral Comprehensive method  
1. Under the Standardised Approach, institutions shall use $\mathrm{E^{*}}$ as calculated under Article 223(5) as the exposure value for the purposes of Article 113. In the case of off-balance sheet items listed in Annex I, institutions shall use $\mathrm{E^{*}}$ as the value to which the percentages indicated in Article 111(1) shall be applied to arrive at the exposure value.  
2. Under the IRB Approach, institutions shall use the effective LGD $(\mathrm{LGD^{*}})$ as the LGD for the purposes of Chapter 3. Institutions shall calculate $\mathrm{LGD^{*}}$ as follows:  
$$
\ L G D^{*}=L G D\cdot{\frac{E^{*}}{E}}
$$  
where:  
$\mathrm{LGD}=$ the LGD that would apply to the exposure under Chapter 3 where the exposure was not collateralised;  
E $\mathbf{\Sigma}=\mathbf{\Sigma}$ the exposure value in accordance with Article 223(3);  
$\mathrm{E^{*}}$ $\mathbf{\Sigma}=\mathbf{\Sigma}$ the fully adjusted exposure value in accordance with Article 223(5).

