(a) money deposits received from the counterparty as collateral;
(b) a payment legs;
(c) underlying debt instruments, to which in each case a capital charge of $1,60\%$ or less applies in accordance with Table 1 of Article 336, institutions shall assign those positions to one of the six hedging sets for each currency set out in Table 4.
